## 10. Property-Based Tests (PBT)

### PBT-01: Exclusion list is complete and immutable

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Field | Value |
| **ID** | PBT-01 |
| **Level** | PBT |
| **Priority** | High |
| **Type** | Property-Based |
| **Requirement** | BR-8 |
| **Property** | For any directory tree, the set of excluded directory names is always exactly {node\_modules, **pycache**, .git, out, dist} |

**Property:** ∀ tree: DirectoryTree → excludedDirs(copyResult(tree)) ⊆ {"node\_modules", "\_\_pycache\_\_", ".git", "out", "dist"}

### PBT-02: Case-sensitivity of exclusion

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Field | Value |
| **ID** | PBT-02 |
| **Level** | PBT |
| **Priority** | High |
| **Type** | Property-Based |
| **Requirement** | BR-9 |
| **Property** | For any directory name that differs in case from exclusion list items, the directory IS copied |

**Property:** ∀ name: string where name ∉ EXCLUDE\_LIST ∧ name.toLowerCase() ∈ EXCLUDE\_LIST.map(toLowerCase) → name IS copied

### PBT-03: Depth-independence of exclusion

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Field | Value |
| **ID** | PBT-03 |
| **Level** | PBT |
| **Priority** | High |
| **Type** | Property-Based |
| **Requirement** | BR-10 |
| **Property** | For any excluded directory name at any depth N, it is never present in the copy output |

**Property:** ∀ depth: N, ∀ excludedName ∈ EXCLUDE\_LIST → path.at(depth) === excludedName → NOT in output

### PBT-04: File vs directory distinction for exclusion

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Field | Value |
| **ID** | PBT-04 |
| **Level** | PBT |
| **Priority** | High |
| **Type** | Property-Based |
| **Requirement** | BR-11 |
| **Property** | For any file whose name matches an exclusion list item, the file IS still copied |

**Property:** ∀ file: File where file.name ∈ EXCLUDE\_LIST ∧ file.isFile() → file IS in output

### PBT-05: Filter exactness — no partial matching

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Field | Value |
| **ID** | PBT-05 |
| **Level** | PBT |
| **Priority** | High |
| **Type** | Property-Based |
| **Requirement** | BR-13 |
| **Property** | For any item in source whose name is a substring/superstring of a filter item but not exact match, it is NOT copied |

**Property:** ∀ item: string, ∀ filter: string[] → item ∉ filter ∧ (item.includes(filter[i]) ∨ filter[i].includes(item)) → item NOT in output

